cs.FL, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT. 

This paper deals with the pumping lemma and Ogden lemma for a specific type of context-free grammar, namely displacement context-free grammars. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the generation of context-sensitive languages, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of stronger variants of the pumping lemma and Ogden lemma may involve statistical analysis, which could place the paper under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the study of well-nested multiple-context free languages, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
